b'I wanted jewelry that would take my gold blazer from formal to trendy, so I decided to layer three necklaces - yes three! First, I started with the burgundy velvet Duchess Choker which is oh-so-fall, then I thought, it needs more... glam. So I added in my Pyramid Spike Y-Chain necklace for length before topping it off with the layered gold Axelia Choker. Together they create the illusion of one super-glamorous statement piece.'

b'I\xe2\x80\x99ve partnered with BaubleBar to style three looks showcasing some of my favorite jewelry trends of the moment: chokers, layered chains and tassels! For my first look, I styled the black bowtie Whitely Choker with gold Caesar Ear Crawlers and a gold Micro Collar necklace. Chokers are huge this season, so I decided to layer two of them for a little extra umph. The gold ear crawlers pair nicely with this combination because they are subtle but still add a bit of sparkle.'

b"Fall is that in between season. It's not quite hot, but it's not quite cold, so we dress for a temperate climate that often varies from one extreme to the other, especially here in Los Angeles. So how do I get through fall looking and feeling my absolute best? With lightweight separates and trends that are endlessly versatile! Gaucho pants are perfect for fall weather because they keep you warm on chilly days (add tights for a little extra warmth!) and they are super breezy in the case of a heatwave. I paired my gauchos with a color blocked sweater and a structured black bag for a tailored-yet-sporty look that is perfect for running around town, shopping, or meeting up with my girlfriends for happy hour. Some people may think of off-duty style as jeans and a t-shirt but I think that you can look casual while still being polished and a bit glamorous!"

b'The plaid pattern in charcoal on this suit is nice and subtle. It works well because the charcoal grey is a darker shade for the season and the bold pattern is much more subtle this way. A great way to break away from the essential grey and navy suits that everyone has in their wardrobe. Setting the bar in the office for what great work style can be. Pair the plaid suit with a purple dot tie for a nice pop, a complementing pattern mix combo. Then step it up with a black monkstrap shoe with the Kilitie.'
b'Read more at: http://www.fashionzenblog.com/'

b'The Navy suit is an essential in any guy\xe2\x80\x99s closet. If there\xe2\x80\x99s one suit you need, the Perry Ellis Very Slim Travel Luxe Tech Suit is it. The Travel Luxe features a comfortable performance stretch fabric for me to wear on my travels. The slim fit suit fits me perfect off the rack especially the pants are slimmed and hemmed at the perfect length and width on my shoes. The suit keeps me looking fresh to and from the airport and straight to a meeting or cocktail hour. The suit also features hidden tech pockets with zipper to secure my important belongings like wallet, phone, documents so nothing gets loose and lost. This is perfect for me and my lifestyle right now since I\xe2\x80\x99ve been constantly on the go from one city to another (NYC-Vegas-LA-NYC-RI-NYC-ATL).'

b"Happy weekend, guys! Here comes my second outfit for NYFW. If you noticed, I'm wearing the same pair of shoes, and it is not because I had no other pair. I actually was so silly, and wore my new sneakers during my flight and got huge blisters. It was the biggest mistake of my life! After getting huge blisters, I couldn't wear any of the other shoes that I brought with me. If you ever plan to travel or go to fashion week, never-ever wear your new shoes on the first night!!!!! Lesson learned!My dear friend Natalia from Australia was so nice and took these photos of me. You should check out her website too (InterlacedMedia)! That night, I wore my Band of Gypsies blouse with denim jumpsuit from Storets. "

b"I always have been a big fan of wide leg pants. I believe I first mentioned this in one of my oldest blog posts. Wide leg pants can be flattering or can make you look even taller. Of course, I always choose them in dark colors because it visually make you look way skinnier and longer. Of course, heels help too. But if you are tall enough, wide leg pants on you will definitely look amazing. As a petite girl, I always envied taller girls like many of you. Tall girls truly can pull off just about anything and they will look great. Being petite is always complicated when finding the correct size. I'm glad there are designers and smart people who realize that not every one looks like a model, and come up with fits that work for all of us. Anyway, I was happy to get my Zara pleated pants that unfortunately were a big longer than I expected. Nothing too hard for my local tailor to fix."

b"One of my favorite trends in menswear is working with neutrals for a tonal look. I decided to take this style on a lighter note at #NYFW Men's since it was getting hot and humid. I was inspired to go with the white and off-white tones for this outfit. Chances are you already have some of these essential items in your closet - white dress shirt, white chino pants, beige linen jacket, and suede loafers. I went with a casual approach with an oxford button-down shirt and worn it untucked (helps with some air flow in the season too!). Paired the look with a clean and sharp pair of white chinos to break up the ensemble. Finished off with some suede tassel loafers that look great dressed up or down. Overall, this neutral tonal look is such a simple refreshing way to rock the summer style."
b'BLOG: http://www.pupuren.com/red-white-cat INSTAGRAM: @pupuren'

b"Forever 21 is one of my favorite stores since 2013! They always have crazy deals and super stylish clothes. Every month, I spend hours and hours to find something special and have never been disappointed. I remember returning two items that weren't perfect. Not so bad, right? I even buy clothes for my sister in Kazakhstan, because she loves this brand too. Sadly, they don't deliver to many countries still. I have been keeping my eye on these striped wide-leg pants since last month, and finally got them along with this printed tee and suede jacket. Thanks Forever 21 for featuring my selfie on their main Instagram page. It was exciting! Today, I wanted to show how you can style these items together in a way that you would never have thought. Wide-leg pants have been very trendy from previous years, and these line up nicely with my big love of striped clothes. Graphic tee\xc2\xa0are a must-have! As for the suede jacket, I love how soft is feels. I will try to style it with a mini skirt for you next time!"
